00:34:05,720 --> 00:34:05,834
Rym: Yep.

496
00:34:06,600 --> 00:34:07,340
Scott: But I would say that that is-.

497
00:34:07,340 --> 00:34:14,679
Scott: But the train was such a revolution that once the train was invented, they built tracks like mad, right?

498
00:34:14,699 --> 00:34:15,681
Scott: They're just like, "Oh my god,

499
00:34:15,722 --> 00:34:16,143
Scott: trains!".

500
00:34:16,203 --> 00:34:24,940
Scott: And we had to build tracks everywhere to the point at which they were, you know, enslaving people and all sorts of horrible things just to get more tracks going to more places.

501
00:34:25,840 --> 00:34:31,271
Rym: Any old city in America, under almost every street, are buried.

502
00:34:31,792 --> 00:34:35,540
Rym: Tons of old tram and train tracks from the pre-car era.

503
00:34:35,880 --> 00:34:44,699
Rym: But also, this whole idea that, "Oh, well, people can go anywhere in a car, but if a train-" Society built itself around trains before there were cars.

504
00:34:44,760 --> 00:34:50,320
Rym: The idea was, if you built a train somewhere, the fact that it's only on those rails is really important.

505
00:34:50,460 --> 00:34:56,739
Rym: There's an idea of infrastructure inertia, where once the track is there, it's hard to move or to get rid of it.

506
00:34:57,100 --> 00:35:04,920
Rym: So, if someone builds a track somewhere, it makes a lot of sense for towns to grow around where there's stations on those tracks.

507
00:35:05,240 --> 00:35:15,717
Rym: So, the map of the train network caused the map of cities and humans existing in America, just like how before trains, rivers caused that.

508
00:35:15,757 --> 00:35:17,380
Rym: That's why every old city is on a river.

509
00:35:18,380 --> 00:35:25,900
Scott: Yep, it's like, hey, you might have a place where no one can live, maybe not because it's not a livable place, but because no one can get there.

510
00:35:26,381 --> 00:35:29,626
Scott: A train track that's going from A to B happens to pass that place.

511
00:35:30,327 --> 00:35:38,820
Scott: Someone can get out there, just one person gets out there, build a train station, the track is there, and suddenly you have settlement happening.

512
00:35:39,320 --> 00:35:42,948
